.TH "_set_clockactivity" 9 "_set_clockactivity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_set_clockactivity \- set OCP_SYSCONFIG.CLOCKACTIVITY bits in @v
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _set_clockactivity
.BI "(struct omap_hwmod *oh "  ","
.BI "u8 clockact "  ","
.BI "u32 *v "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "oh" 12
struct omap_hwmod *
.IP "clockact" 12
CLOCKACTIVITY field bits
.IP "v" 12
pointer to register contents to modify
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the clockactivity mode bits in \fIv\fP to be \fIclockact\fP for the
\fIoh\fP hwmod.  Used for additional powersaving on some modules.  Does
not write to the hardware.  Returns -EINVAL upon error or 0 upon
success.
